instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The framework defines a lifecycle comprising (1) device modeling within BIM where sensors, actuators, and controllers are added; (2) model enrichment and extraction using model‑driven engineering (MDE) to produce structured representations; (3) automatic generation of deployable DT artifacts; (4) deployment of the twin and establishment of real‑time data exchange for continuous synchronization; (5) runtime operation with interactive visualization; and (6) post‑deployment extension via standardized extension points for custom services. Transition between phases is managed automatically by the MDE pipeline, and lifecycle governance is assigned to the three actor roles—Building Control Engineer (modeling and control‑logic definition), Facility Manager (monitoring and operation), and DT Engineer (service integration)."
